section.section:
The Division shall deduct from the inmate's earnings in the following order of priority:
an amount the Division determines to be the cost to the State of providing food, lodging, and clothing for the inmate;
fees assessed under § 2-118 of this article;
the actual and necessary food, travel, and other expenses of the inmate when released from actual confinement under the work-release program;
subject to paragraph (3) of this subsection, any amount that the inmate is legally obligated to pay to support the inmate's dependents; and
the amount that a court orders to be paid as restitution.
